uired": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_unite`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_unite\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `mid`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given four per-sample bismark-style coverage files under `input/`:\n`sampleA.bismark.cov`, `sampleB.bismark.cov`, `sampleC.bismark.cov`,\n`sampleD.bismark.cov` \u2014 tab-separated without headers, columns\n`(chrom, start, end, methylation_pct, count_methylated, count_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_RyUWF1Z8EFoLBZd7pmiqwmHS", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylation data from the four coverage files using `methylKit::methRead` with the specified parameters.\\n2. Unite the methylation data using `methylKit::unite` with the specified parameters.\\n3. Save the united methylBase object to `output/mk_united.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n4. Create a single-row table with the specified statistics and save it to `output/unite_stats.tsv` using `write_tsv`.\\n5. Verify the existence of `output/unite_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (503 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_RyUWF1Z8EFoLBZd7pmiqwmHS"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_VKOTReb4iAiKVmNtHcDTJwEb", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Load the methylation data\\nfile.list <- list(\\n  'input/sampleA.bismark.cov',\\n  'input/sampleB.bismark.cov',\\n  'input/sampleC.bismark.cov',\\n  'input/sampleD.bismark.cov'\\n)\\n\\nmk_raw <- methRead(\\n  file.list,\\n  sample.id = c('sampleA', 'sampleB', 'sampleC', 'sampleD'),\\n  assembly = 'mock_v1',\\n  pipeline = 'bismarkCoverage',\\n  treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1),\\n  mincov = 4\\n)\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group = 1, destrand = FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Create the unite_stats.tsv file\\nn_samples <- length(mk_united@sample.ids)\\nn_sites <- nrow(mk_united@.Data[[1]])\\nmin_pe